Gameplay development is in progress. Fleet remains to be constructed. Design has shifted from server-side board to client-side boards becaue of GameControllers and how they already require substantial client-side processing for game play.
Need to assemble the fleet onto the client's GUI grid. Code must be written for this.

Updating Ship, Fleet, and Spot methods to work together logically. Identifying need to implement Service, Worker, and Task resources for network IO, as Platform.runLater is not ideal for this, and in fact may be causing issues.
Rewriting placeShips to use java8's stream() and collectors etc.
Rewriting placeShips to use java8's stream() and collectors etc.

Ship placement works. Rewrote the method from scratch using streams and collections. Took the previous 327 lines (which could only place two of the eight ships in a fleet) and condensed it down to 79 lines that do it all. This update marks a big step forward in my understanding of the Java 8 stream API. I can now begin moving forward on other areas of the project.

Network interface and object transmission needs work. Interfaces are bulky and should probably be rewritten to be leaner. Cannot get the top grid button text values to change from ~, most likely because of issues in transmitting the AttackResult objects (and in receiving them, etc.). They aren't registering. Need to address this next.

To the best of my knowledge at this point, everything works. Server is configured to receive clients on port 1500. battleship.jdzcode.com has been forwarded to my public ip at home, and port 1500 has been forwarded to Shadowfax for hosting internet battleship sessions. Initial tests are showing success.
